# 4. おしゃれは楽しく

Kanade: Umm... Pardon the intrusion.
Ichika: Pardon us.
Saki: Enter! Welcome, Kanade, Ichi♪
Saki: Thank you again for agreeing to come all this way, Kanade.
Saki: I promise to really capture your radiance today!
Kanade: *Nod* Thank you for having me.
Kanade: (I'm a little nervous... I hardly ever go over to other people's houses.)
Kanade: (Still...)
Saki: Kanade?
Kanade: Oh, I'm sorry... I was just marveling at how well-organized your room is...
Saki: Huh? You really mean that?
Kanade: Yes, my room is so cluttered... Things literally come crashing down on top of me sometimes.
Saki: What?! I hope you've never gotten hurt!
Kanade: No, since it's never anything heavy... Mostly sheet music and cardboard boxes...
Kanade: Once I find the inspiration for a song, I'll start working on that right away and make things like cleaning my room take a back seat.
Ichika: I understand what you mean. It's like nothing else matters besides the song you're writing.
Saki: Haha. I have this habit of throwing everything into my closet when I don't really have time. Unfortunately for me, that's resulted in a few avalanches.
Saki: *Gasp* Please, sit down! You two don't have to keep standing!
Saki: I've also prepared snacks and drinks, so have as much as you like!
Kanade: Oh wow... It's like we're having a little party...
Ichika: Hm? This pile of magazines...
Saki: Heh heh heh! They're the fashion magazines I've gathered!
Saki: Remember the pictures I took of you the other day after we left the cafe, Kanade?
Kanade: Oh, yes... You said you were going to use them to prepare for today...?
Saki: That's right! I found a cool trick in this one video I saw...
Saki: You print out pictures of your friend and place them where a model's face is supposed to go, and...
Ichika: Oh wow. It's like she's all dressed up now.
Saki: This helps you get a clear picture of what your friend would look like wearing a particular outfit!
Kanade: I see...
Ichika: That is pretty cool. I might give this a try with my own picture sometime...
Saki: You totally should! This is so much easier than trying on clothes at an actual shop, which means more fun combinations to test!
Saki: I tried mixing and matching different pieces of outfits using this trick...
Kanade: Oh, there's a sticky note on this page...
Saki: Hehe. This is my first candidate!
Saki: I thought the idea of having a monotone outfit accented by flashy accessories was kinda cool.
Ichika: Yeah, this is pretty cool... It's like something a rock star would wear.
Kanade: Do you really think I'll be able to pull this off...?
Saki: I know you will! Oh, but this one's a bit more girly!
Ichika: Yeah, it's cute. Like one of those poofy dresses you see on dolls.
Kanade: Yes, I think Mizuki would really like this one.
Saki: Hehe. I thought the same thing♪ You can make it even cuter by adding a brooch to this hat.
Saki: Oh, if you're feeling brave, I thought we could also try a sporty look...
Saki: Anyway, I'm hoping that we can take pictures of you wearing a few of these outfits!
Kanade: Okay, that seems fine.
Ichika: I don't know much about fashion, but I do think that you'll look good in all of these, Kanade...
Saki: Me too! I've even come up with hairstyles and makeup ideas for each one♪
Saki: Oh, I know. Can I try doing your hair right now, Kanade?
Kanade: I don't mind, but I'm still in my sweats. Is that okay...?
Saki: Yes! I want to take this opportunity to get a feel for your hair!
Saki: Let's see... I have my brush, hairpins and... Oh, am I gonna need oil for this?
Ichika: Hehe. Saki's so excited...
Kanade: *Nod*
Kanade: (I know that she wants to do well on her project...)
Kanade: (But she must love fashion very much.)
Saki: Thank you for waiting!
Saki: I'll start by combing your bangs.
Kanade: Okay, I'm ready whenever...
Saki: Your hair's so silky and smooth, Kanade.
Saki: But it's also super long. Isn't maintaining it really hard?
Kanade: I don't actually do much to maintain it... It's also long because that's just easier for me.
Saki: Wait, your hair's naturally this silky smooth...?!
Saki: That's incredible... My hair's been sorta wavy since I was little, so I have this fascination with perfectly straight hair.
Ichika: But I like your hair, Saki. It's so fluffy and soft.
Kanade: I agree. It matches your personality really well.
Saki: Hehe. Thank you♪
Saki: But a part of me has always wanted to do something about my wavy hair. That's why I began learning what I could about styling from magazines and stuff.
Saki: Because when you get your hair and outfit just right, it's like a sign that you're going to have a great day!
Kanade: (A sign that you're going to have a great day...)
Kanade: (I've never seen things from that sort of perspective before.)
Saki: I'm thinking about going with a half-up, half-down hairstyle that flows naturally.
Saki: If you had your choice of ringlets or buns, which would you prefer?
Kanade: Uhh... I'll leave that up to you.
